HEADWORD: Porous
<hw>Por"ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>poreux</ets>. See <er>Pore</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>Full of
pores; having interstices in the skin or in the substance of the body;
having spiracles or passages for fluids; permeable by liquids; <as>as, a
<ex>porous</ex> skin; <ex>porous</ex> wood.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧The veins
of <xex>porous</xex> earth.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Porously</ent>⟦br⟧
